{% # Validation - Preset - Hero v2.1.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v2.1.0 — expand to three labelled hero variants (configuration robustness, per `validation-contract.md` Tier 3) + render `validation--block-labels` with the media inside-label exception (media is overflow:hidden + full-bleed, so the shared above-block label is clipped). Variants make the authoring principle visible: `centered-full` + `bottom-left` carry a taller `mobile_media_size` (4:5) so a full hero's content fits the narrow-viewport box; `short-fit` keeps 16:9 at both viewports to show short content fits a wide box. The mobile clipping was an authoring mistake (too-short box for the content), caught by the new content-fits QA guard — not a reason to make media content-driven.
  - v2.0.0 — first real Tier-3 implementation (was a stale scaffold predating the grid-bleed model + several block-API changes). token-section is now the real production theme-root grid (drop the `display: block` override) so the media block's bleed actually paints via grid-column. Fixture reconciled to current block APIs: media `bleed_desktop`/`bleed_mobile` enums (was the removed `bleed` boolean) + the `custom_color_scheme` gate (v1.5.0), richtext `content_width` (was the removed `narrow`), a real seeded hero image. Harness chrome from `validation--harness-styles`. Per `validation-contract.md` Tier 3.
  - v1.0.0 — initial scaffold (composition reference; not tracked as a Tier-3 implementation)

  Tier-3 composition validation for the "hero" pattern: three labelled full-bleed
  media variants, each with an overlaid title + body + button inside the media's
  <media-contents> overlay. Exercises the cross-block cascade integration that
  only emerges in composition:

  - Bleed paints: the media escapes the content track to the section's bleed
    boundary (grid-column: bleed-start / bleed-end), at both viewports.
  - Color-scheme override at block level: a media carries scheme-3 (light on
    dark); its child title / body / button re-resolve scheme-3 tokens, not the
    section's scheme-1 (`short-fit` inherits the section scheme — no override).
  - Overlay tint paints over the (real, seeded) image, below the contents.
  - <media-contents> alignment (center vs the bottom-start default) + gap.
  - Content fits its box: a too-short box for the content clips silently (media
    is overflow:hidden + media-driven by design) — authors size the box
    (incl. mobile_media_size) to fit; the suite guards this as the QA mechanism.

  Reachable only at /?view=validation--preset--hero.
  See `.context/docs/validation.md` + `validation-contract.md` § Tier 3.
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign color_scheme = section.settings.color_scheme | default: 'scheme-1'
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root,color-scheme:{{ color_scheme }}">
  {% render 'validation--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class="validation__intro">
    <h1>Composition: hero</h1>
    <p>
      Three labelled full-bleed <code>media</code> variants with overlaid title + body + button.
      <code>centered-full</code> and <code>bottom-left</code> override the section's scheme-1 with scheme-3
      (light-on-dark) and carry a taller <code>mobile_media_size</code> so their content fits the narrow box;
      <code>short-fit</code> inherits scheme-1 and keeps 16:9 at both viewports (short content fits a wide box). Tier-3
      asserts the cascade-applied result, and guards that content fits its box (a too-short box is an authoring mistake,
      caught here — not media's burden to absorb).
    </p>
  </header>

  {% content_for 'blocks' %}

  {% render 'validation--block-labels', section: section %}
</token-section>

{% render 'validation--harness-styles' %}

{% stylesheet %}
  @layer components {
    /* media is overflow:hidden, clipping the shared above-the-block label;
       place it inside the top-left instead (same exception as the media page).
       The `[data-modifiers]` qualifier (always present on media) lifts this over
       the shared label rule's specificity. */
    .shopify-section--validation--preset--hero token-section > .shopify-block--media[data-modifiers]::before {
      inset-block-start: 0.5rem;
      inset-block-end: auto;
      inset-inline-start: 0.5rem;
      z-index: 1;
      padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem;
      border-radius: 0.25rem;
      background-color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.85);
      color: #1a1a1a;
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Preset: hero",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--validation--preset--hero",
  "blocks": [{ "type": "@theme" }],
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "Color scheme",
      "default": "scheme-1"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
